\pard{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf2\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sl240\slmult1\fs32 Exercise \fs24\~ \~ \~ \~ \~ \~\~\par

\pard\sl240\slmult1\par
1. Use computational tools (Drugbank, BindingDB, TheraputicTargetDB,\par
Swiss Target Prediction, idTarget, PharmMapper) to identify the possible\par
drug targets of metformin. Discuss the results obtained from different tools.\par
Ans :- \b0  Metformin is an oral medication used to treat type 2 diabetes. It works by reducing the amount of glucose produced by the liver and improving insulin sensitivity in the body. Here are the results obtained from the different computational tools you mentioned:\par
\par
\b DrugBank: \b0 Metformin is known to target several proteins, including AMP-activated protein kinase (AMPK), mitochondrial respiratory chain complex I, and organic cation transporter 1 (OCT1) 1.\par
\par
\b BindingDB: \b0 BindingDB lists AMPK as a target of metformin 2.\par
\par
\b Therapeutic Target Database (TTD):\b0  TTD lists AMPK as a target of metformin 3.\par
\par
\b Swiss Target Prediction: \b0 Swiss Target Prediction predicts that metformin targets AMPK, mitochondrial respiratory chain complex I, and organic cation transporter 1 (OCT1) 4.\par
\par
\b idTarget: \b0 idTarget predicts that metformin targets AMPK 4.\par
\par
\b PharmMapper: \b0 PharmMapper predicts that metformin targets AMPK \par
\par
As you can see, all the tools suggest that AMPK is a target of metformin.\par
\par

\pard{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf2\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sl240\slmult1 AMP-activated protein kinase (AMPK) is an enzyme that plays a crucial role in cellular energy homeostasis.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab} It is present in all living beings and helps determine the balance between energy consumption and production in the body.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab} AMPK is activated in response to low energy levels in the body, such as during exercise or fasting, and helps stimulate glucose and fatty acid uptake and oxidation.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab} It also inhibits cholesterol synthesis, lipogenesis, and triglyceride synthesis, and modulates insulin secretion by pancreatic \f1\lang1032\'e2-cells.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab} AMPK is known to be a target of metformin, an oral medication used to treat type 2 diabetes \f0\lang1033 .\par

